      "message": "the \"-fPIC -fno-common\" flags are added by the Configure script when building the shared libraries. You need to look inside the script to see why. This allows us to use -no-shared while being able to link everything. -fPIC actually defines compiler macros (e.g. __PIC__) that are picked by the assembly language sources\n\nBoth solutions should be equivalent, except we don\u0027t rebuild shared libraries at all.",
